01:27:50,625 --> 01:27:52,583
<i>I sincerely hope...</i>

1296
01:27:53,500 --> 01:27:55,542
<i>the Senate makes the right vote tomorrow</i>

1297
01:27:55,625 --> 01:28:00,083
<i>so that Alex Murphy's sacrifices
will not have been in vain.</i>

1298
01:28:04,917 --> 01:28:07,042
<i>Senator Dreyfus is my friend.</i>

1299
01:28:07,125 --> 01:28:10,125
<i>He has been my mentor and my strength</i>

1300
01:28:10,208 --> 01:28:12,083
<i>in times of difficulty on this floor.</i>

1301
01:28:13,083 --> 01:28:15,708
<i>But despite all that,
I work for the state of Ohio,</i>

1302
01:28:16,083 --> 01:28:18,833
<i>and the safety of
its citizens is my top priority.</i>

1303
01:28:19,708 --> 01:28:20,958
<i>So I vote yes.</i>

1304
01:28:21,042 --> 01:28:22,917
<i>The Dreyfus Act must be repealed.</i>

1305
01:28:23,583 --> 01:28:25,917
That's us ahead, 39 to 10.

1306
01:28:26,000 --> 01:28:28,917
Yeah, I spoke to the Senate liaison
and it looks like it's in the bag,

1307
01:28:29,000 --> 01:28:31,333
but we still have to tread
carefully with the politicians.

1308
01:28:33,542 --> 01:28:35,833
<i>We're here live
at DPD headquarters</i>

1309
01:28:35,917 --> 01:28:37,625
<i>where moments ago, Ciara Murphy</i>

1310
01:28:37,708 --> 01:28:40,000
<i>- made a shocking statement.</i>
- What the hell?

1311
01:28:40,083 --> 01:28:44,833
<i>OmniCorp has denied me and my son
access to Alex for weeks.</i>

1312
01:28:45,625 --> 01:28:47,250
<i>I demand to know why.</i>

1313
01:28:48,625 --> 01:28:53,292
<i>This treatment is inhuman and somebody
needs to be held accountable.</i>

1314
01:28:54,583 --> 01:28:56,583
Oh, we're fucked.

1315
01:28:56,667 --> 01:28:58,083
No, we only need 12 votes.

1316
01:28:58,167 --> 01:28:59,750
She shouldn't make much difference.

1317
01:28:59,833 --> 01:29:01,708
Yeah,
but what about after the vote?

1318
01:29:01,792 --> 01:29:04,125
I mean, those two
should not be allowed contact.

1319
01:29:04,208 --> 01:29:06,708
If she starts putting ideas in his head...

1320
01:29:06,792 --> 01:29:09,333
Bring her in. I'll handle the explanation.

1321
01:29:09,417 --> 01:29:11,000
And what about Alex?

1322
01:29:11,083 --> 01:29:13,243
You know, unfortunately,
we can't just keep him on ice.

1323
01:29:14,000 --> 01:29:16,417
The shooting at the station
spooked some of the politicians.

1324
01:29:16,500 --> 01:29:18,667
They're our clients.
We have to take care of them.

1325
01:29:19,042 --> 01:29:21,792
They're fine when a machine
is lowering the murder rate,

1326
01:29:21,875 --> 01:29:26,125
but when a man is investigating
city politics, they get nervous.

1327
01:29:26,208 --> 01:29:28,417
All right. First off,
it's not a man, okay?

1328
01:29:28,500 --> 01:29:30,500
It's property of OmniCorp.

1329
01:29:30,583 --> 01:29:32,917
And politics are
the least of your concern.

1330
01:29:33,000 --> 01:29:34,640
I mean, this thing solved its own murder.

1331
01:29:34,708 --> 01:29:37,059
How long till it realizes
you haven't been on the level with it?

1332
01:29:37,083 --> 01:29:38,375
If that happens,

1333
01:29:38,458 --> 01:29:41,208
every journalist in this country
is dying to speak to him.

1334
01:29:41,292 --> 01:29:43,083
I mean, we created a hero.

1335
01:29:44,000 --> 01:29:46,333
What happens when he opens his mouth?

1336
01:29:50,042 --> 01:29:51,625
What's bigger than a hero?

1337
01:30:03,417 --> 01:30:04,500
Dead hero.

1338
01:30:08,958 --> 01:30:10,833
Get me Dr. Norton.

1339
01:30:20,000 --> 01:30:21,250
What is this, Raymond?

1340
01:30:21,917 --> 01:30:26,375
You have Mattox spying on me and now this
bullshit about a "critical condition"?

1341
01:30:26,458 --> 01:30:29,208
You know and I know Alex is fine!

1342
01:30:29,292 --> 01:30:30,667
Calm down.

1343
01:30:30,750 --> 01:30:32,208
Dennett.

1344
01:30:32,292 --> 01:30:33,572
Your work is so good, I don't...

1345
01:30:33,625 --> 01:30:35,018
Well, now, this is not about my work!

1346
01:30:35,042 --> 01:30:37,083
You saw the woman on TV!

1347
01:30:37,167 --> 01:30:38,792
This has to stop!

1348
01:30:41,083 --> 01:30:42,083
You're right.

1349
01:30:43,042 --> 01:30:45,292
But let me ask you something, Dennett.

1350
01:30:45,375 --> 01:30:47,667
What kind of life have
we really given Alex Murphy?

1351
01:30:47,750 --> 01:30:51,292
He's never gonna be a normal man,
a father, a husband.

1352
01:30:51,375 --> 01:30:54,667
By the time we put the other units
on the street, he's just...

1353
01:30:54,750 --> 01:30:55,792
Dennett.

1354
01:30:57,833 --> 01:30:58,917
Let's face it.

1355
01:30:59,958 --> 01:31:01,292
We failed him.

1356
01:31:03,042 --> 01:31:04,792
We failed Alex Murphy.

1357
01:31:04,875 --> 01:31:06,755
But I want you to think
about the bigger picture

1358
01:31:06,792 --> 01:31:08,458
'cause that's what we're talking about.

1359
01:31:08,542 --> 01:31:11,167
The work you've done with him
is gonna be studied for decades.

1360
01:31:11,250 --> 01:31:13,375
You've changed
the face of history, Dennett.

1361
01:31:13,458 --> 01:31:17,875
No policeman is ever going to die
in the line of duty again

1362
01:31:18,500 --> 01:31:19,833
'cause of you.

1363
01:31:21,750 --> 01:31:23,042
You think about that.

1364
01:31:31,667 --> 01:31:35,667
I want that family taken care of

1365
01:31:35,750 --> 01:31:37,125
beyond their wildest dreams.

1366
01:31:37,208 --> 01:31:38,917
- We owe them that.
- I agree.

1367
01:31:40,042 --> 01:31:42,750
I want full funding. 10 years.

1368
01:31:43,917 --> 01:31:45,542
New staff, all my own people.

1369
01:31:45,625 --> 01:31:46,917
Fantastic.

1370
01:31:47,875 --> 01:31:48,875
Deal.

1371
01:31:59,250 --> 01:32:00,917
Hey. What's going on?

1372
01:32:01,000 --> 01:32:02,840
Security's here.
They're clearing everyone out.

1373
01:32:02,917 --> 01:32:04,208
They're not waking him up.

1374
01:32:04,750 --> 01:32:06,708
Whatever you do, don't leave him alone.

1375
01:32:06,792 --> 01:32:08,472
What do you mean
they're not waking him up?

1376
01:32:10,125 --> 01:32:11,542
<i>The voting period has ended.</i>

1377
01:32:11,625 --> 01:32:14,208
<i>The clerks have tabulated the results.</i>

1378
01:32:14,292 --> 01:32:16,375
<i>The yeas are 63.</i>

1379
01:32:16,458 --> 01:32:18,292
<i>The nays are 22.</i>

1380
01:32:19,083 --> 01:32:21,333
<i>A majority of senators
have voted in the affirmative.</i>

1381
01:32:21,917 --> 01:32:24,958
<i>The Dreyfus Act has
been repealed by Congress.</i>

1382
01:32:31,250 --> 01:32:33,458
God, you guys are slow,
like a bunch of girls.

1383
01:32:33,542 --> 01:32:34,667
This is Mattox.

1384
01:32:34,750 --> 01:32:36,208
<i>Dennett's on board.</i>

1385
01:32:36,292 --> 01:32:37,500
It's about time.

1386
01:32:43,083 --> 01:32:44,083
Call it.

1387
01:32:44,917 --> 01:32:46,125
<i>Get it done.</i>

1388
01:32:47,250 --> 01:32:48,250
My pleasure.

1389
01:32:57,375 --> 01:32:59,708
- Mrs. Murphy...
- You can come here as much as you want.

1390
01:32:59,792 --> 01:33:02,958
You can threaten me.
You can sue me. You can take my home,

1391
01:33:03,042 --> 01:33:06,417
but I am not gonna stop till I see
my husband. Do you understand that?

1392
01:33:06,500 --> 01:33:08,625
Mr. Sellars would
very much like to see you.

1393
01:33:10,583 --> 01:33:12,250
Is Alex okay?

1394
01:33:12,333 --> 01:33:15,167
He has important information to share
with you. Will you accompany me?

1395
01:33:18,167 --> 01:33:19,167
David.

1396
01:33:21,083 --> 01:33:22,875
We gotta go. Can you grab your coat?

1397
01:33:22,958 --> 01:33:25,250
Hey!

1398
01:33:25,333 --> 01:33:26,773
<i>I'm in the elevator, on my way down.</i>

1399
01:33:26,833 --> 01:33:28,250
I need access to the lab.

1400
01:33:28,333 --> 01:33:29,693
That's insane. They're still here.

1401
01:33:30,000 --> 01:33:31,583
<i>Distract them.</i>

1402
01:33:31,917 --> 01:33:33,000
Okay.

1403
01:33:34,333 --> 01:33:35,458
I cannot...

1404
01:33:35,542 --> 01:33:37,375
There's a lady in here going hysterical.

1405
01:33:37,458 --> 01:33:39,559
She will not let us in.
She's got the codes for the door.

1406
01:33:39,583 --> 01:33:41,292
I repeat, she will not let us in.

1407
01:33:41,375 --> 01:33:43,684
Lady, you need to let us in there now.
We have to get in there.

1408
01:33:43,708 --> 01:33:45,351
Are you not understanding what I'm saying?

1409
01:33:45,375 --> 01:33:48,292
Do you wanna be responsible for
the deaths of everyone in this building?

1410
01:33:48,375 --> 01:33:49,375
Hey! Stop!

1411
01:33:53,792 --> 01:33:54,958
Don't shoot!

1412
01:33:55,042 --> 01:33:56,208
Step outside.

1413
01:34:02,833 --> 01:34:04,375
Unlock the transmitter!

1414
01:34:05,875 --> 01:34:07,000
Transmitter unlocked!

1415
01:34:14,542 --> 01:34:16,333
Send in Mrs. Murphy, please.

1416
01:34:16,417 --> 01:34:17,708
<i>Right away, sir.</i>

1417
01:34:20,125 --> 01:34:21,125
<i>Wake him up!</i>

1418
01:34:21,875 --> 01:34:24,667
Alex! Alex!

1419
01:34:25,167 --> 01:34:28,375
Alex, it's Dr. Norton,
you have to wake up!

1420
01:34:28,458 --> 01:34:29,625
Alex, can you hear me?

1421
01:34:31,167 --> 01:34:32,708
These men are here to kill us!

1422
01:34:32,958 --> 01:34:35,208
They're here to kill us, for Christ sakes!

1423
01:34:40,375 --> 01:34:41,833
<i>Mrs. Murphy, last night,</i>

1424
01:34:41,917 --> 01:34:43,583
Alex had a psychotic break.

1425
01:34:44,250 --> 01:34:48,250
He killed an unarmed colleague
and later suffered a seizure.

1426
01:34:49,792 --> 01:34:51,042
We did everything,

1427
01:34:51,125 --> 01:34:54,417
everything we could,
but the doctors couldn't save him.

1428
01:34:55,667 --> 01:34:58,000
Very sorry, Mrs. Murphy.

1429
01:34:58,083 --> 01:35:00,043
We're going to be
making the announcement shortly.

1430
01:35:01,083 --> 01:35:03,375
You shut me down.
I was about to get a confession.

1431
01:35:03,958 --> 01:35:05,083
Mattox shut you down.

1432
01:35:07,125 --> 01:35:09,542
I've removed your transmitter
so he won't do it again.

1433
01:35:10,333 --> 01:35:12,000
Sellars can't afford to wake you up.

1434
01:35:13,583 --> 01:35:15,542
He sent these guys to pull the plug.

1435
01:35:16,250 --> 01:35:19,417
He wants you dead,
Alex. Do you understand?

1436
01:35:19,875 --> 01:35:21,542
Sorry.
If there's anything we can do

1437
01:35:21,625 --> 01:35:23,083
for you and David, we'll do it.

1438
01:35:23,167 --> 01:35:24,750
I want nothing from you.

1439
01:35:26,458 --> 01:35:27,542
I understand.

1440
01:35:28,250 --> 01:35:29,833
You stay out of our lives.

1441
01:35:32,000 --> 01:35:33,542
You and your company.

1442
01:35:33,625 --> 01:35:34,945
If that's what you think is best.

1443
01:35:36,167 --> 01:35:37,542
There's one more thing.

1444
01:35:37,625 --> 01:35:40,750
I think it would be to the benefit
of everyone, especially David,

1445
01:35:40,833 --> 01:35:42,833
if we kept this matter private.

1446
01:35:42,917 --> 01:35:45,292
We don't wanna damage Alex's legacy.

1447
01:35:48,292 --> 01:35:50,500
<i>Alex! Alex!</i>

1448
01:35:50,583 --> 01:35:51,792
I can fix this!

1449
01:35:52,250 --> 01:35:53,542
You lied to me.

1450
01:35:53,833 --> 01:35:54,958
You lied to my wife.

1451
01:35:55,292 --> 01:35:57,059
You're working for
the people that are trying to kill me.

1452
01:35:57,083 --> 01:35:59,833
- You want me to trust you, Doctor?
- Alex, I can go to the press!

1453
01:36:01,667 --> 01:36:04,167
Alex, I can tell them the whole story!

1454
01:36:04,708 --> 01:36:05,708
Alex!

1455
01:36:06,500 --> 01:36:07,833
Listen to me, please!

1456
01:36:09,417 --> 01:36:12,458
Alex! Alex!

1457
01:36:24,292 --> 01:36:25,333
What the hell?

1458
01:36:33,833 --> 01:36:35,273
Keep all our systems at green light,

1459
01:36:35,333 --> 01:36:37,250
and for Christ sakes,
get Sellars on the phone.

1460
01:36:37,333 --> 01:36:38,375
<i>Roger that.</i>

1461
01:36:38,458 --> 01:36:40,417
Damn, damn, damn, damn, damn!

1462
01:36:41,792 --> 01:36:43,000
Look at this city.

1463
01:36:45,333 --> 01:36:46,500
So beautiful.

1464
01:36:47,625 --> 01:36:49,833
It's become so peaceful.

1465
01:36:53,208 --> 01:36:54,333
I wish...

1466
01:36:55,583 --> 01:36:57,500
I had some good news for Detroit.

1467
01:36:58,208 --> 01:37:00,208
I have very sad news.

1468
01:37:00,292 --> 01:37:02,750
Despite our best efforts to save him,

1469
01:37:03,167 --> 01:37:05,542
Alex Murphy passed away just hours ago.

1470
01:37:06,125 --> 01:37:07,250
Alex Murphy...

1471
01:37:07,333 --> 01:37:08,792
Mr. Sellars.

1472
01:37:08,875 --> 01:37:10,542
- What is it?
- Mattox just called.

1473
01:37:11,125 --> 01:37:12,625
We need you to come with us now.

1474
01:37:19,208 --> 01:37:21,226
Ma'am, I need you to turn around
and go the other way, please.

1475
01:37:21,250 --> 01:37:23,268
- What are you talking about?
- We have a security situation here.

1476
01:37:23,292 --> 01:37:25,018
I need you to turn around
and go the other way.

1477
01:37:25,042 --> 01:37:26,143
Sir, there's a car outside...

1478
01:37:26,167 --> 01:37:27,958
That area is locked down. Now go.

1479
01:37:28,042 --> 01:37:29,750
- What's happening?
- I said go!

1480
01:37:30,458 --> 01:37:32,000
I wanna talk to Mr. Sellars.

1481
01:37:35,292 --> 01:37:36,292
Mr. Sellars.

1482
01:37:36,667 --> 01:37:37,917
How close is that helicopter?

1483
01:37:38,000 --> 01:37:39,042
About 10 minutes, sir.

1484
01:37:56,417 --> 01:37:57,833
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

1485
01:37:57,917 --> 01:38:00,208
I need to speak with Sergeant Jack Lewis.

1486
01:38:00,292 --> 01:38:01,667
It's an emergency.

1487
01:38:01,833 --> 01:38:03,833
Stand by. Mr. Sellars.

1488
01:38:03,917 --> 01:38:05,757
Apparently there's
a Ciara Murphy in the lobby.

1489
01:38:06,208 --> 01:38:09,000
Raymond, if she sees him,
we are dead in the water.

1490
01:38:09,083 --> 01:38:10,083
What do you wanna do?

1491
01:38:10,458 --> 01:38:11,625
Bring Mrs. Murphy up here.

1492
01:38:11,708 --> 01:38:12,708
Yes, sir.

1493
01:38:16,708 --> 01:38:19,625
Norton said they may be
using drones for protection.

1494
01:38:19,708 --> 01:38:21,833
So whatever you do,
do not draw your weapons.

1495
01:38:21,917 --> 01:38:24,333
They won't shoot if we're unarmed. Clear?

1496
01:38:24,417 --> 01:38:25,625
Clear.

1497
01:38:42,042 --> 01:38:43,292
Hold it right there.

1498
01:38:43,375 --> 01:38:45,375
Don't move.

1499
01:38:47,958 --> 01:38:52,458
This is private property.
You are not authorized to be here!

1500
01:38:56,333 --> 01:38:58,625
I'd put those guns down now if I were you.

1501
01:38:58,708 --> 01:39:00,868
- Stand down.
- All right, man, we're good, we're good.

1502
01:39:03,083 --> 01:39:04,083
Go, back it up!

1503
01:39:47,167 --> 01:39:48,167
Head to the lower level.

1504
01:39:49,750 --> 01:39:50,833
Hold up, hold up!

1505
01:39:50,917 --> 01:39:52,000
Ram it!

1506
01:40:52,375 --> 01:40:53,417
Gun it.

1507
01:40:55,042 --> 01:40:56,500
Go, go, go! Now!

1508
01:41:12,625 --> 01:41:13,958
Alex, run!

1509
01:41:15,125 --> 01:41:17,083
OmniCorp Security!
Drop your weapons!

1510
01:41:17,167 --> 01:41:18,917
<i>Drop your weapon.</i>

1511
01:41:19,333 --> 01:41:22,292
<i>Keep your hands above your head
and no one will be harmed.</i>

1512
01:41:37,292 --> 01:41:38,458
What's going on?

1513
01:41:38,542 --> 01:41:40,917
Mrs. Murphy,
I want you to listen to me carefully.

1514
01:41:41,000 --> 01:41:43,500
The organic part of
your husband Alex is dead.

1515
01:41:43,583 --> 01:41:45,750
The robotic part of him is malfunctioning,

1516
01:41:45,833 --> 01:41:47,059
and he's shooting up the building.

1517
01:41:47,083 --> 01:41:49,667
So we've gotta get you and your son
out of here right away.

1518
01:41:49,750 --> 01:41:51,125
I gotta take this call.

1519
01:41:52,417 --> 01:41:54,292
He just left the lobby
and he's headed our way.

1520
01:41:54,375 --> 01:41:55,583
<i>Roger that, sir.</i>

1521
01:41:56,375 --> 01:41:58,042
Don't shoot. My robot.

1522
01:41:58,125 --> 01:41:59,500
- You just flank.
- Got it.

1523
01:41:59,583 --> 01:42:00,833
Tin Man.

1524
01:42:03,625 --> 01:42:04,833
Tin Man.

1525
01:42:05,792 --> 01:42:07,000
Tin Man.

1526
01:42:07,417 --> 01:42:08,583
Oh, there it is.

1527
01:42:09,458 --> 01:42:10,625
You look like crap.

1528
01:42:13,458 --> 01:42:14,542
What's the matter?

1529
01:42:14,625 --> 01:42:15,833
Can't shoot?

1530
01:42:17,625 --> 01:42:18,625
Huh?

1531
01:42:19,458 --> 01:42:21,208
What were you thinking?
This isn't a drill.

1532
01:42:21,375 --> 01:42:22,625
You're a robot.

1533
01:42:22,875 --> 01:42:25,667
I'm a red asset. Wrote that myself.

1534
01:42:25,750 --> 01:42:26,750
What do you think?

1535
01:42:27,500 --> 01:42:30,292
Come on, Tin Man, just pull the trigger.

1536
01:42:30,375 --> 01:42:31,375
Pull it.

1537
01:42:32,125 --> 01:42:33,417
You can run.

1538
01:42:33,917 --> 01:42:34,958
Go on.

1539
01:42:35,042 --> 01:42:36,083
Run.

1540
01:42:36,667 --> 01:42:37,917
Run!

1541
01:42:38,000 --> 01:42:39,750
There you go. Run.

1542
01:42:40,375 --> 01:42:42,000
Run. Run!

1543
01:42:44,708 --> 01:42:45,958
Whoo!

1544
01:42:46,375 --> 01:42:48,375
Stings like a bitch, don't it?

1545
01:42:48,708 --> 01:42:51,583
Aren't you lucky I didn't
have my gun set to "kill"?

1546
01:42:53,167 --> 01:42:54,792
Hey, listen.

1547
01:42:54,875 --> 01:42:56,083
This isn't personal.

1548
